## Where is `noise_modifier_fm.txt`?

The 21,954-pattern annotation dictionary used by Filter 1 lives in the
Python package itself:

    cleantest_agent/data/noise_modifier_fm.txt

This is the **single source of truth**. The previous duplicate copy in
this directory has been removed to avoid drift between the two files
and to keep the open-source repository ~1.7 MB lighter.

`cleantest_agent.pipeline` resolves the dictionary path automatically
via `importlib.resources` (see the docstring of
`_resolve_noise_modifier_path()` in `cleantest_agent/pipeline.py`), so
no skill or downstream user has to know this path explicitly.

If you really want a hard copy of the file inside the skill folder
(e.g. for an air-gapped deployment), regenerate it with:

```bash
python -c "import importlib.resources, shutil; \
shutil.copy(importlib.resources.files('cleantest_agent').joinpath('data/noise_modifier_fm.txt'), \
            'skills/cleantest-syntax-filter/references/noise_modifier_fm.txt')"
```
